Class TTimeData

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.traveltime.TTimeData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TTimeData>

    public class TTimeData
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<TTimeData>
    Holds everything known about one seismic phase at a particular source depth and source-receiver distance.

    Ray Buland

        public TTimeData(java.lang.String phCode,
                 double tt,
                 double dTdD,
                 double dTdZ,
                 double dXdP,
                 boolean corrTt)
        The constructor accepts basic travel time information.
        Parameters:
        phCode - Phase code
        tt - Travel time
        dTdD - Derivative of time with respect to distance
        dTdZ - Derivative of time with respect to depth
        dXdP - Derivative of distance with respect to ray parameter
        corrTt - True if the travel-time itself needs to be modified by the statistical bias

        public void addFlags(java.lang.String phGroup,
                     java.lang.String auxGroup,
                     boolean isRegional,
                     boolean isDepth,
                     boolean canUse,
                     boolean dis)
        Add phase flags.
        Parameters:
        phGroup - Base phase group
        auxGroup - Auxiliary phase group
        isRegional - True if this is a regional phase
        isDepth - True if this is a depth phase
        canUse - True if this phase can be used in an earthquake location
        dis - True if this phase should be down weighted during phase identification
